  "text": "# Elasticsearch Index Lifecycle Management (ILM) Architecture Analysis\n\n## Overview\nThe Elasticsearch 8.17.0 ILM system is a comprehensive policy-driven index management framework. The implementation spans across three main components: core policy definitions, ILM coordination service, and cluster state management.\n\n## Core Components\n\n### 1. Policy Model Classes (x-pack/plugin/core/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/xpack/core/ilm/)\n\n**LifecyclePolicy** (LifecyclePolicy.java)\n- Represents the lifecycle of an index from creation to deletion\n- Contains a mapping of phase names to Phase objects\n- Implements SimpleDiffable<LifecyclePolicy> and ToXContentObject for serialization\n- Supports TimeseriesLifecycleType and validates phases through LifecycleType\n- Includes optional metadata and deprecation flags\n\n**Phase** (Phase.java)\n- Represents a set of LifecycleActions to execute at a particular point in index lifecycle\n- Contains minimum age (TimeValue) and a map of named LifecycleActions\n- Implements ToXContentObject and Writeable for serialization\n- Ordered by LifecycleType; actions execute in defined order\n\n**Step** (Step.java)\n- Abstract base class for all ILM execution steps\n- Contains StepKey (phase, action, name) and next step reference\n- Subclassed into four main step types:\n  - ClusterStateActionStep: Updates cluster state, immediate execution\n  - ClusterStateWaitStep: Waits for cluster state condition\n  - AsyncActionStep: Performs asynchronous actions via client\n  - AsyncWaitStep: Periodically checks asynchronous conditions\n\n### 2. Step Execution Framework\n\n**ClusterStateActionStep** (ClusterStateActionStep.java)\n- Abstract class for steps that modify cluster state directly\n- Method: performAction(Index, ClusterState) -> ClusterState\n- Optional indexForAsyncInvocation() for spawning new indices\n- Executed synchronously during cluster state update tasks\n\n**ClusterStateWaitStep** (ClusterStateWaitStep.java)\n- Abstract class for steps that wait on cluster state conditions\n- Method: isConditionMet(IndexMetadata, ClusterState) -> boolean\n- Fast-path for checks not requiring async operations\n- Included in periodic policy execution\n\n**AsyncWaitStep** (AsyncWaitStep.java)\n- Abstract class for periodically-evaluated async conditions\n- Method: evaluateCondition(Metadata, Index, Listener, TimeValue)\n- Listener callbacks: onResponse(boolean, ToXContentObject) and onFailure(Exception)\n- Used for checks that may require I/O (e.g., segment count, rollover readiness)\n\n**AsyncActionStep** (AsyncActionStep.java)\n- Abstract class for async actions via transport/client calls\n- Method: performAction(IndexMetadata, ClusterState, ClusterStateObserver, ActionListener<Void>)\n- indexSurvives() indicates if action deletes the index\n- Used for operations like rollover, shrink, force-merge, delete\n\n### 3. ILM Service (Policy Evaluator)\n\n**IndexLifecycleService** (x-pack/plugin/ilm/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/xpack/ilm/IndexLifecycleService.java)\n- Implements ClusterStateListener, ClusterStateApplier, SchedulerEngine.Listener\n- Triggers policy evaluation: scheduled via SchedulerEngine and on cluster changes\n- Key method: clusterChanged(ClusterChangedEvent) - filters indices and dispatches to IndexLifecycleRunner\n- Maintains master-only scheduler for policy evaluation\n- Handles cluster state lifecycle events and index creation\n- Integrates with PluginShutdownService for graceful shutdown\n\n### 4. Policy Execution Engine\n\n**IndexLifecycleRunner** (IndexLifecycleRunner.java)\n- Executes individual step operations from PolicyStepsRegistry\n- Dispatches step execution to appropriate method based on step type:\n  - ClusterStateActionStep: submitUnbatchedTask(ExecuteStepsUpdateTask)\n  - AsyncWaitStep: evaluateCondition() with periodic re-evaluation\n  - AsyncActionStep: performAction() with client\n  - ClusterStateWaitStep: immediate condition check\n- Handles step failure, retry logic, and error step transitions\n- Updates LifecycleExecutionState in index metadata\n\n**PolicyStepsRegistry** (PolicyStepsRegistry.java)\n- Central registry mapping policy names to compiled step sequences\n- Maintains: lifecycle policy map, first step cache, step lookups\n- Updates dynamically as policies change via update(Metadata)\n- Parses phase definitions from IndexLifecycleMetadata\n- Provides: getStep(IndexMetadata, StepKey), getIndexAgeForPhase(policy, phase)\n\n### 5. Cluster State Update Tasks\n\n**ExecuteStepsUpdateTask** (ExecuteStepsUpdateTask.java)\n- Extends IndexLifecycleClusterStateUpdateTask\n- Executes ClusterStateActionStep operations\n- Updates metadata with new step keys and execution state\n- Deduplicates identical transitions\n\n**MoveToNextStepUpdateTask** (MoveToNextStepUpdateTask.java)\n- Transitions index to next step after async action completes\n- Updates LifecycleExecutionState with new StepKey\n- Validates transition legality via IndexLifecycleTransition\n\n**IndexLifecycleTransition** (IndexLifecycleTransition.java)\n- Validates step transitions and policy phase changes\n- moveClusterStateToNextStep(IndexMetadata, StepKey) -> ClusterState\n- Manages phase caching via PhaseCacheManagement\n- Handles policy metadata versioning\n\n### 6. Execution State Storage\n\n**LifecycleExecutionState** (server/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/cluster/metadata/LifecycleExecutionState.java)\n- Record-based immutable state containing:\n  - Current: phase, action, step\n  - Error tracking: failedStep, isAutoRetryableError, failedStepRetryCount\n  - Metadata: stepInfo, previousStepInfo, phaseDefinition\n  - Timestamps: lifecycleDate, phaseTime, actionTime, stepTime\n  - Context-specific: snapshotRepository, snapshotName, shrinkIndexName, downsampleIndexName\n- Serialized as custom metadata in IndexMetadata via ILM_CUSTOM_METADATA_KEY (\"ilm\")\n- Builder pattern for construction and modification\n\n**IndexMetadata** (server/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/cluster/metadata/IndexMetadata.java)\n- Contains LifecycleExecutionState via getLifecycleExecutionState()\n- Stores lifecycle policy name and execution state\n\n### 7. Transport Actions (Policy Management)\n\n**TransportPutLifecycleAction** (x-pack/plugin/ilm/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/xpack/ilm/action/TransportPutLifecycleAction.java)\n- Extends TransportMasterNodeAction<PutLifecycleRequest, AcknowledgedResponse>\n- Handler: UpdateLifecyclePolicyTask (AckedClusterStateUpdateTask)\n- Validates policy format via NamedXContentRegistry\n- Updates IndexLifecycleMetadata in cluster state\n- Handles policy version management and index metadata updates\n- Supports SearchableSnapshotAction and WaitForSnapshotAction validation\n\n**TransportDeleteLifecycleAction** (x-pack/plugin/ilm/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/xpack/ilm/action/TransportDeleteLifecycleAction.java)\n- Extends TransportMasterNodeAction<Request, AcknowledgedResponse>\n- Handler: DeleteLifecyclePolicyTask (AckedClusterStateUpdateTask)\n- Removes policy from IndexLifecycleMetadata\n- Ensures no indices reference deleted policy\n\n### 8. Additional ILM Actions\n\n- TransportGetLifecycleAction: Retrieves stored policies\n- TransportExplainLifecycleAction: Explains current execution state of indices\n- TransportMoveToStepAction: Manual step transitions\n- TransportRetryAction: Retries failed steps\n\n### 9. Metadata Management\n\n**IndexLifecycleMetadata** (IndexLifecycleMetadata.java)\n- Cluster-wide container for all ILM policies\n- Map<String, LifecyclePolicyMetadata> storing policy metadata\n- OperationMode tracking (RUNNING, STOPPED, STOPPING)\n\n**LifecyclePolicyMetadata** (LifecyclePolicyMetadata.java)\n- Wrapper around LifecyclePolicy with versioning\n- Stores: policy name, version, creation time, last modified time\n- Used for policy update detection and consistency\n\n**PhaseCacheManagement** (PhaseCacheManagement.java)\n- Manages cached phase definitions in index metadata\n- Prevents execution interruption when policies are updated\n- Methods: refreshPhaseDefinition(), updateIndicesForPolicy()\n\n## Execution Flow\n\n1. **Policy Trigger**: IndexLifecycleService.clusterChanged() fires on cluster events or scheduled interval\n2. **Index Discovery**: Service filters indices with active ILM policies\n3. **Registry Lookup**: PolicyStepsRegistry provides current step for index\n4. **Step Execution**:\n   - ClusterStateActionStep: Immediate cluster state update via ExecuteStepsUpdateTask\n   - AsyncActionStep: Client action dispatch via IndexLifecycleRunner\n   - AsyncWaitStep: Async condition evaluation with periodic re-check\n   - ClusterStateWaitStep: Immediate condition evaluation\n5. **State Transition**: Successful step completion triggers MoveToNextStepUpdateTask\n6. **Error Handling**: Failures transition to ErrorStep and await manual retry\n\n## Key Design Patterns\n\n- **Immutable State**: LifecycleExecutionState is a record for thread-safe mutations\n- **Registry Pattern**: PolicyStepsRegistry centralizes step lookup and caching\n- **Composite Steps**: Steps compose into phases and policies\n- **Listener Pattern**: AsyncWaitStep and AsyncActionStep use callbacks for completion\n- **Cluster Task Deduplication**: IndexLifecycleRunner deduplicates identical transitions\n- **Phase Caching**: PhaseCacheManagement isolates indices from concurrent policy updates\n"
}

